    {
      "id": "PopularPost122292",
      "post_content": "Were I to use it, [Leyline of the Void](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leyline of the Void) all the way.  \n  \n@dream\\_spinner  \nLotV only hits opponent's graveyards, so you can get rid of it; but they'll have to kill the enchantment to.  \n  \nEDIT:   \nYears later.. I think I used to look at some of these cards to seriously. This is a fun little card. IMO, because it's fun, let's make a deck around making it fun. How about [Opalescence](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Opalescence) and [rite of replication](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=rite of replication). Now each of you get creatures when exchanging. You can even really confuse things by responding on the stack in-between trigger resolutions that way you split up the now-six enchantment-creatures.   \n  \nGo big or go home right?",
      "posted_by": "blurrymadness",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost122292\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">Were I to use it, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Leyline of the Void\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leyline of the Void\">Leyline of the Void</a> all the way.<br/><br/>@dream_spinner<br/>LotV only hits opponent's graveyards, so you can get rid of it; but they'll have to kill the enchantment to.<br/><br/>EDIT: <br/>Years later.. I think I used to look at some of these cards to seriously. This is a fun little card. IMO, because it's fun, let's make a deck around making it fun. How about <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Opalescence\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Opalescence\">Opalescence</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"rite of replication\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=rite of replication\">rite of replication</a>. Now each of you get creatures when exchanging. You can even really confuse things by responding on the stack in-between trigger resolutions that way you split up the now-six enchantment-creatures. <br/><br/>Go big or go home right?</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '122292'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy44651\">blurrymadness</span>\r\n                                (8/10/2